    "description": "A synthetic sulfite preservative that releases sulfur dioxide (SO2) when dissolved in water. Commonly used in winemaking to prevent oxidation and microbial growth. Can cause asthma attacks in sensitive individuals and destroys vitamin B1 (thiamine) in foods."
  },
  "manufacturing": {
    "method": "chemical synthesis",
    "description": "Produced by passing sulfur dioxide gas through a solution of potassium carbonate or potassium hydroxide."
  },
